        "unit": "ns",
        "value": 20,
        "description": "Nanosecond regime preferred for Teak to minimize heat-affected zone (HAZ) while ablating contaminants; picosecond (ps) or femtosecond (fs) reduce thermal damage further but are costlier; 20 ns typical for wood cleaning (e.g., laser physics research in Applied Surface Science, 2019). Avoid fs for industrial scale due to complexity."
      },
