        "description": "Effective speeds for 1064 nm cleaning of wood; recommended 2000 mm/s for optimal contaminant removal without excessive heat buildup on Teak; lower for heavy contamination (500-1000 mm/s), higher for light (3000-5000 mm/s) per industry standards (e.g., Laserax equipment manuals and Journal of Applied Physics, 2020)."
